728270f-d.title: Queens: Yellowstone Boulevard - Dartmouth Street
728270f-d.text:
Yellowstone Boulevard (formerly white Pot Road), east side,
between Dartmouth and Clyde Streets, showing in 4 views the
Abraham Furman farmhouse. The homestead of Caspar Springstein,
who settued here about 1700 was opposite the Furman property on
the west side of the Boulevard. The buildings seen on the west
side of dlte Pot Road at about Burns Street are no longer in
existent in 1925. They were the property of David Springstein
in 1909. See other views.
1922
Views 1,2,3 and 4.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection
